						<summary>

						<p>On a slab lying in a field one mile to the south of the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1161, Vishu-saṅkrānti.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of land for conducting worship and providing offerings to the image of Sakalēśvaradēva by Gaṇḍapeṇdāra Gaṅgeya Sāhiṇi.</p>						

